Sentencas: The cathode-electrolyte interface in a solid oxide fuel cell is examined to understand why premature delamination is observed in alumina substituted YSZ electrolyte.
Titulo: Effect of alumina additions in YSZ on the microstructure and degradation of the LSM-YSZ interface

Sentencas: SEM and TEM observations it was concluded that after high temperature sintering a tetragonal (Mn,Al)(3)O(4) forms at the interface, which during prolonged fuel cell operation forms a cubic (Mn,Al)(3)O(4) phase.
Titulo: Effect of alumina additions in YSZ on the microstructure and degradation of the LSM-YSZ interface

Sentencas: This transformation is associated with volume decrease creating voids which ultimately weaken the cathode-electrolyte interface sufficiently for the cathode layer to delaminate off the YSZ-Al(2)O(3) electrolyte.
Titulo: Effect of alumina additions in YSZ on the microstructure and degradation of the LSM-YSZ interface
